<header>
  <div class="wrap reveal">
    <span class="eyebrow">● Creative Strategist · High Blood Pressure / Hypertensive Retinopathy</span>
    <h1>Welcome to <span class="hl">Neurobella</span>.<br>Let's build winners.</h1>
    <p class="sub">You're our new <strong>Direct Response Creative Strategist &amp; Copywriter</strong>. You'll own one angle — <strong>Hypertensive Retinopathy</strong> — across <strong>three avatars</strong>. This page is your operating system. Read it top to bottom before your first brief.</p>
    <div class="hero-kpi">
      <div class="kpi"><div class="n">25</div><div class="l">Briefs / week (total)</div></div>
      <div class="kpi"><div class="n">3</div><div class="l">Avatars</div></div>
      <div class="kpi"><div class="n">50%</div><div class="l">Min hook rate (KPI)</div></div>
      <div class="kpi"><div class="n">25%</div><div class="l">Min hold rate (KPI)</div></div>
      <div class="kpi"><div class="n">1.25</div><div class="l">Min ROAS target</div></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</header>

<!-- MISSION -->
<section id="mission">
  <div class="wrap reveal">
    <span class="sec-tag">01 — Your Mission</span>
    <h2>Produce 25 high-converting briefs every week</h2>
    <p class="lead">Turn proven psychology into a constant stream of testable native ads and videos for the <strong>Hypertensive Retinopathy</strong> angle. Build on real avatars, the mechanism, pains and desires, then read the data and feed the next batch. Every concept is judged against the same bar: <strong>≥ 50% hook rate</strong>, <strong>≥ 25% hold rate</strong> and <strong>≥ 1.25 ROAS</strong>.</p>

    <div class="grid g2" style="margin-top:24px">
      <div class="angle-card" style="--ac:#ff8a4c">
        <h3>📰 Native ads</h3>
        <p style="color:var(--ink);font-size:15px;margin-top:8px;font-weight:650">18 native ads / week</p>
      </div>
      <div class="angle-card" style="--ac:#5cc8ff">
        <h3>🎬 Video ads</h3>
        <p style="color:var(--ink);font-size:15px;margin-top:8px;font-weight:650">7 videos / week</p>
        <p style="color:var(--muted);font-size:13px;margin-top:4px">VSL · AI VSL · UGC · Animation style</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p class="lead" style="margin-top:14px;font-size:14.5px"><strong>Weekly total:</strong> 18 native + 7 video = <strong>25 briefs</strong>, all on the Hypertensive Retinopathy angle.</p>

    <div class="grid g3" style="margin-top:22px">
      <div class="card"><h3><span class="chip">🎯</span>3 Avatars</h3><p>One angle, three avatars (A, B and 3). Same mechanism, symptoms and pains — only the avatar and desire change.</p></div>
      <div class="card"><h3><span class="chip">📰</span>Native &amp; Video</h3><p>Write tight native-ad advertorials and video scripts (VSL, AI VSL, UGC, animation) at the right awareness level.</p></div>
      <div class="card"><h3><span class="chip">📈</span>Learnings</h3><p>After each batch is tested, you read the data and write the learnings. They shape the next 25.</p></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- PRINCIPLE -->
<section>
  <div class="wrap reveal">
    <div class="banner">
      <div class="big">⚙️</div>
      <div>
        <h3>The #1 rule: don't reinvent the wheel</h3>
        <p>We already know what works in the ad account. Your starting point is always the <strong>existing winning combinations</strong> — the avatar + desire + pain + mechanism pairings that already produced winners. Build on proven psychology first; vary with intention.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- MASTER SHEET -->
<section id="sheet">
  <div class="wrap reveal">
    <span class="sec-tag">02 — The Brain</span>
    <h2>The Creative Master Sheet</h2>
    <p class="lead">One sheet is the source of truth. It holds every past winning ad with a full breakdown so you never start from a blank page. You'll get a Loom walkthrough — keep it organized and log all your work here. <strong>The Master Sheet is internal only</strong> (you, the founder, and Claude). Editors never touch it — they receive their tasks in Notion.</p>
    <div class="grid g4">
      <div class="card"><h3>🏆 Winning Ads</h3><p>Every ad that won in the account, with what made it work.</p></div>
      <div class="card"><h3>🧠 Avatar &amp; Desire</h3><p>The avatar and core desire behind each winner.</p></div>
      <div class="card"><h3>💢 Pain &amp; Symptoms</h3><p>The exact pains and symptoms the ad spoke to.</p></div>
      <div class="card"><h3>🔬 Mechanism &amp; Format</h3><p>The hook, mechanism and the winning creative format.</p></div>
    </div>
    <p class="lead" style="margin-top:18px"><strong>Study the Legend tab</strong> too — it lists every concept level, creative format and iteration code. You're expected to know which formats are currently winning in the market. Before creating anything, ask of each winner: <em>why did it work, why not?</em> Form a hypothesis, then build.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- LEVELS -->
<section id="levels">
  <div class="wrap reveal">
    <span class="sec-tag">03 — The System</span>
    <h2>The 5 Concept Levels</h2>
    <p class="lead">Every brief is tagged with a concept level. <strong>You always start at Level 2.</strong> Then, as learnings come in, you move into Levels 3, 4 and 5 on the winners. <strong>Level 1 is not in your scope</strong> — net-new concepting is handled by the founder/team.</p>
    <div class="levels">
      <div class="level locked" style="--lv:#ff6b6b;--lv2:#ff8a4c">
        <div class="lv-badge">1</div>
        <div><h3>Net New Concepts <span class="tag-mini tag-lock">🔒 Not your scope</span></h3><p>Completely new angles or mechanisms unseen in the ad account (sourced from Kalodata, organic, competitors, etc.). Owned by the founder/team — not part of your weekly output.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="level" style="--lv:#f5c451;--lv2:#ff8a4c">
        <div class="lv-badge">2</div>
        <div><h3>New Structural Formats <span class="tag-mini tag-go">▶ Start here</span></h3><p>Same mechanism / angle / desire, delivered in a <strong>different script format or narrative style</strong> — e.g. testimonial-driven, UGC storyline, advertorial, etc. This is your default entry point for every avatar. Go to <strong>AdSpy</strong> to spy on winning creatives and source the <strong>new structural formats</strong> worth modeling.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="level" style="--lv:#b8f04a;--lv2:#1fd07a">
        <div class="lv-badge">3</div>
        <div><h3>Major Variations on Winners <span class="tag-mini">After learnings</span></h3><p>Same core idea, adjusted for a <strong>new symptom, desire, avatar or tone</strong> — e.g. pain relief → mobility, AI voice → doctor, swapped mechanism.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="level" style="--lv:#1fd07a;--lv2:#0fa860">
        <div class="lv-badge">4</div>
        <div><h3>Lead / Stitch Variations <span class="tag-mini">After learnings</span></h3><p>Variations on winning concepts — creating "Level 4" <strong>lead / stitch</strong> variations on the winners.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="level" style="--lv:#0fa860;--lv2:#0b7a48">
        <div class="lv-badge">5</div>
        <div><h3>Hook Variations <span class="tag-mini">After learnings</span></h3><p>Variations on winning concepts — creating "Level 5" <strong>hook</strong> variations to keep fresh creative running and fight fatigue while scaling.</p></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- FORMATS & CODES -->
<section id="formats">
  <div class="wrap reveal">
