    <!-- SYMPTOMS -->
    <div class="group-label">Symptoms — swipe language</div>
    <div class="test-list">
      <div class="test-row"><div class="cond">Blurry / hazy central vision</div><div class="sym">Comes and goes, then slowly worsens.</div></div>
      <div class="test-row"><div class="cond">Dark / blurry spot in the center</div><div class="sym">The “sink-drain blind spot” (scotoma) that swallows faces and text.</div></div>
      <div class="test-row"><div class="cond">Straight lines bending &amp; warping</div><div class="sym">Doorframes and book lines looking wavy — the “funhouse mirror” / “melting letters” effect.</div></div>
      <div class="test-row"><div class="cond">Floaters &amp; dark specks / clouds <span class="status st-new">Use with care</span></div><div class="sym">Drifting across the vision.</div></div>
      <div class="test-row"><div class="cond">Glare &amp; halos at night</div><div class="sym">Headlights starbursting; fear of night driving.</div></div>
      <div class="test-row"><div class="cond">Duller, washed-out, faded colors</div><div class="sym">The world losing its color.</div></div>
      <div class="test-row"><div class="cond">Can't read fine print even with the right glasses</div><div class="sym">Squinting under a brighter and brighter lamp.</div></div>
      <div class="test-row"><div class="cond">Trouble recognizing faces</div><div class="sym">Across a room — or even up close.</div></div>
      <div class="test-row"><div class="cond">Sudden double vision &amp; “behind-the-eye” headaches</div><div class="sym">The “hypertensive pulse.”</div></div>
      <div class="test-row"><div class="cond">Temporary blackouts <span class="status st-new">Emergency — handle with care</span></div><div class="sym">Vision goes dark for minutes.</div></div>
      <div class="test-row"><div class="cond">Constant stinging &amp; burning</div><div class="sym">The “chlorine pool water in my eyes” feeling.</div></div>
      <div class="test-row"><div class="cond">Gritty, sandy irritation</div><div class="sym">“Sand under my eyelids” — worst on waking.</div></div>
      <div class="test-row"><div class="cond">Waking at 2–3am with bone-dry, burning eyes</div><div class="sym">…and a jolt of panic.</div></div>
      <div class="test-row"><div class="cond">Tired, heavy, raw eyes by end of day</div><div class="sym">The dry-eye cluster hits Avatar 3 especially (several meds dry the ocular surface) and is a daily reality for B.</div></div>
    </div>

    <!-- PAIN POINTS -->
    <div class="group-label" style="color:var(--orange)">Pain Points — Treatment Trauma &amp; Dread <span style="color:var(--muted-2);font-weight:600;text-transform:none;letter-spacing:0">· lived reality for B · a feared future for A &amp; 3</span></div>
    <div class="test-list">
      <div class="test-row"><div class="cond">The cold metal speculum</div><div class="sym">Clamping the eyelid open.</div></div>
      <div class="test-row"><div class="cond">The needle coming down toward the eye</div><div class="sym">The anticipation worse than the act.</div></div>
      <div class="test-row"><div class="cond">The gritty “sand-in-the-eye” burn</div><div class="sym">For hours after an injection.</div></div>
      <div class="test-row"><div class="cond">Pressure spikes &amp; the post-injection blackout</div><div class="sym">The terrifying minutes of darkness after.</div></div>
      <div class="test-row"><div class="cond">Laser like “staring into a barcode scanner”</div><div class="sym">And it quietly takes night and side vision.</div></div>
      <div class="test-row"><div class="cond">Expensive drops (Restasis / Xiidra)</div><div class="sym">That just burn and barely work.</div></div>
      <div class="test-row"><div class="cond">Stuck on a “medical treadmill”</div><div class="sym">Endless, recurring, costly procedures that never cure anything.</div></div>
    </div>

    <div class="group-label" style="color:var(--gold)">Pain Points — Daily-Life Losses</div>
    <div class="test-list">
      <div class="test-row"><div class="cond">Losing the driver's license</div><div class="sym">And the shame of asking family for rides.</div></div>
      <div class="test-row"><div class="cond">Giving up reading, writing, drawing, painting</div><div class="sym">The hobbies that need sharp vision.</div></div>
      <div class="test-row"><div class="cond">Can't see a loved one's face clearly</div><div class="sym">Spouse, child, or grandchild.</div></div>
      <div class="test-row"><div class="cond">Trouble with stairs, curbs, depth perception</div><div class="sym">Small humiliations and near-falls.</div></div>
      <div class="test-row"><div class="cond">Quietly “testing” their own eyes</div><div class="sym">The street-sign test, covering one eye in secret panic.</div></div>
    </div>

    <div class="group-label" style="color:var(--red)">Pain Points — Emotional &amp; Existential</div>
    <div class="test-list">
      <div class="test-row"><div class="cond">The paralyzing fear of total darkness <span class="status st-main">Master fear</span></div><div class="sym">The “dark couch” — sitting blind while life happens around them.</div></div>
      <div class="test-row"><div class="cond">Terror of becoming a helpless burden</div><div class="sym">Isolated, the thing their family has to care for.</div></div>
      <div class="test-row"><div class="cond">Loss of independence = loss of dignity &amp; identity</div><div class="sym">Who they are, slipping with their sight.</div></div>
      <div class="test-row"><div class="cond">Self-blame &amp; shame <span class="status st-new">Hero pain</span></div><div class="sym">“I did this to myself” — often made worse by a rushed specialist who blames them to their face. The mechanism lifts it: <strong>it was never your fault.</strong></div></div>
      <div class="test-row"><div class="cond">Feeling like an assembly-line product</div><div class="sym">A billing code, not a person.</div></div>
      <div class="test-row"><div class="cond">Deep distrust of pharma</div><div class="sym">Pricing, insurance denials, and the “cash-cow” eye-injection machine.</div></div>
      <div class="test-row"><div class="cond">Financial dread</div><div class="sym">$400-a-shot co-pays, $1,000-a-month drops, all out of pocket.</div></div>
      <div class="test-row"><div class="cond">Isolation, low mood, despair <span class="status st-new">Handle with care</span></div><div class="sym">For some, a real slide toward despair — handle sensitively.</div></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

